  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively buying this dip as SPX has broken below the massive 6575 gamma wall (-2.2% in 1-min) while remaining well above the 6499 flip strike, keeping them in PIN regime where they provide liquidity against the move. The thick positive gamma walls stacked from 6570-6585 (all 1200M+) should act as magnets pulling price back toward fair value, with dealers selling any bounce back into the 6575-6580 zone. Watch for mean reversion strength if we hold above 6570, but a break below this level could accelerate selling toward the 6499 flip where dealer behavior shifts from stabilizing to amplifying.",
